rComments: Lectures are dry and I had difficulty understanding what the prof was saying. However the course material is relatively easy to understand. There are 4 lab exercises, each worth 10% of your grade, midterm is 20% and final is 40%. Tests are easy if you study, and you can do really well on the lab assignments if you visit TA office hours for help.
why finals always use the similar past test questions but the answers are different, I am quite confused about it. although I finally got A-minus, I should get at least A.

This professor does have an accent but I enjoyed listening to him nevertheless. He gives detailed explanations and testing is mostly lecture-based.  He accommodates any issues student have throughout the course.  However, his lecture time of three hours is way too long.

Paying attention in class is essential. I took this as a breadth requirement- science is not my forte and I would've failed if I didn't go and ask him for help. He was over the top helpful and explained things so well. I loved the content and his lecture style. I got sick and he had no trouble accommodating me. I loved him!!
Has a thick accent so hard to understand and lectures will feel long. Interesting material however and not much reading. Exams all multiple choice. Easy A.

Unfortunately his English is so broken that it is impossible to determine what exactly it is he is trying to say. I can't even tell if the material is hard or not because I literally have no idea what sentences are coming out of his mouth. Its frustrating, and he has no idea this is a problem.

As much as the professor tries to clarify and explain all the concepts, it's quite difficult and laborious to fathom his lectures through broken English. His three hour lectures (most people attend for the iClicker marks) can be reduced to one hour; my biggest tip is to just read and take notes from the book.

He eased off the exams from previous year, this year I am taking was so easy almost everyone got over 70%. Materials mainly on lectures slides, many fundamentals great for future courses. He is a great teacher if you go his office hrs he explains everything with you. I got 81% and 100% on two assignments, mid-term 70% final I expect 70%.
